Last night, we discussed "Self-Care: Your Body is a Temple" in our Webinar. I've been working out and eating well consistently since I was 19. However, I have not been practicing self care the whole time. To be honest, most of my wanting to eat the right thing and look a certain way was motivated by my desire to be accepted and esteemed by highly others. I now know you can do all the right things externally and even eat the "right" foods, but still miss what self-care is all about.

Hear me: It's possible to go through all the rigours of exercise and healthy diets but still have disconnection, disdain, and even hatred for yourself, just like it's possible to say and do all the right stuff but not embody the Truth. 
Self-care begins from the inside. It starts with aligning your thoughts, words and actions. It means communicating your truth openly. It means standing up for your self and setting boundaries. I've found that real Self-care starts in my unseen life and manifests in how I reverence my temple.

Coincidence? I think not! We act as a "black hole" with high levels of intense gravity when we embody euphoric, magical, synchronistic, and magical possibilities and attract more of it into our abyss. 🤔🙏 It's important to "expect miracles" it's the weirdest thing but the "universe" will keep on handing em out!! Let's play! 
Love vibrations

How to Get OUT of Depression: In my new YouTube vid I talk about... you know what?! You don't even have to watch it. Here! Here are the 3️⃣ strategies I used and continue to use. Set your timer for two minutes and then implement these.
1️⃣MOVE!!!! Get Physical! Get your blood flowing.
2️⃣Get Social! Call and text people (calling is best). Say anything. Say hi. Sign up for something you enjoy. Like crossfit, jujitsu, running club then you're hitting two birds with one stone.Go to a park, a store, anywhere and greet people.
3️⃣Get Present!! Focus on your senses. Get aware of your environment! Listen to the sounds. Smell the smells. Look at the colors. Sacred breath of this moment.

Buses arrive late. People don’t always answer their emails on time. Planes sometimes do not leave on schedule. Traffic jams can delay your journey home. Our on-time dreams are often shattered.  But what is never late? What is always exactly on time, never too early, never cancelled? What is never delayed? What can never disappoint you? What have you always been waiting for? What has always been here, closer than breathing, prior to concepts of time, of early and late and cancelled? What are you inseparable from?  What has always been waiting for you to stop waiting for it? And what has allowed the waiting anyway?  This moment, exactly as it is. Your true home. Ever-present.  Present thoughts, sensations, feelings, sounds. This sacred breath. No delays reported. – Jeff Foster

Too often self doubt is the only reason we fail to achieve our goals. Recognize that you are in control of this.

Take the control back and try the above exercise. See how it changes your journey.

It's so easy to get weighed down by the past... to feel it's pain, it's beauty, it's tenderness, and it's loss.... But if you can bring yourself to do it, put yourself back in this moment right now, know that you did your very best then, and try to come to a grateful place in your heart that accepts the imperfections of yesterday....You may not have what you had yesterday, but tomorrow you won't possess what you have today.
